Social Media Web Application (Backend)
Overview

+ This project is a backend system for a social media web application, developed independently using Python, Django, and Django REST Framework.
+ The system is built with an API-first architecture, focusing on scalability, security, and extensibility.
It supports core social media features such as authentication, posts, social interactions, activity logging, and real-time chat.
+ This is a personal project with a broad scope, developed alongside continuous learning and research, and is currently under active development.

ðŸ›  Tech Stack
Backend: Python,Django, Django REST Framework
Frontend: JavaScript, HTML, CSS

+ Authentication & Security:
JWT Authentication (SimpleJWT)
dj-rest-auth for API-based login/logout
django-allauth (Google OAuth2 login)
django-axes + ipware (brute-force protection, IP-based lockout)
CORS & CSP configuration for API security
Email verification & password reset via SMTP (Gmail)

+ Core Features: User & Profile

View, update, and delete user profiles
Admin access to all profiles
User settings management

+ Posts & Content

CRUD APIs for posts and articles
Upload multiple images per post (multipart/form-data)
Post visibility based on friendship, follow, and block rules
Pagination, filtering, searching, and ordering
Admin access to all posts

+ Comments & Reactions

Create, update, delete comments
Like / reaction system on posts
Filter reactions by type
User activity tracking on content interactions

+ Social Interactions

Friend request system:
Send, accept, reject, cancel, unfriend
Follow / unfollow users
Block / unblock users
Full permission checks to prevent invalid actions
Automatic cleanup of relationships when blocking users

+ Activity & Logging

User activity stream using django-activity-stream
Action logging (actor, verb, target, timestamp)
Admin log monitoring
Paginated activity history APIs

+ Real-time Chat System

One-to-one conversation creation
Message sending, editing, and unsending
Conversation membership permissions
Message seen/read tracking
Conversation list & message history APIs
Optimized queries with select_related and prefetch_related
Built with Django Channels & Redis

+ API Capabilities

JWT-based authentication
Scoped rate throttling for spam prevention
Filtering, searching, and ordering with django-filter
Multipart & JSON request parsing
Auto-generated API documentation with drf-spectacular

+ Development & Performance

Pagination strategies for large datasets
Query optimization (select_related, prefetch_related)
Django Silk integration for performance profiling
Structured logging for monitoring and debugging

+ Key Libraries Used (Selected)

django-rest-framework

dj-rest-auth

django-allauth

django-axes

django-cors-headers

django-guardian

django-activity-stream

Django Channels + Redis

Celery (background tasks)

drf-spectacular

Additional libraries are used for performance optimization, admin enhancements, testing, and future feature expansion.

+  Future Plans & Roadmap

Advanced Authentication & Security such as 2FA, CAPCHA, CLOUDFLARE

Advanced Post & Content Features such as bookmark functionality, restore posts, scheduled post publishing or academic articles with PDF export and post visibility levels

Real-time & Social Enhancements such as sharing images in chat,  online/offline presence tracking in real time 

Reactions, Comments & Engagement such as real-time like and reaction updates and star rating system for acedemic posts

Notifications & Events such as background task processing using **Celery**

Search & Discovery

Image & Media Processing

Analytics & Monitoring

AI & Third-party Integrations

Deployment & Scalability

Mobile Development (Long-term)